==English==
===Etymology===
Turkish, from Arabic {{ARchar|[[عبريق]]}} ''‘ibrīq'', from Persian ''ābrīz'', from ''āb'' ‘water’ + ''rīz'' ‘cup’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /ɪb'ɹi:k/

===Noun===
'''ibrik'''
# a long-handled Turkish [[coffee]]-pot
#:*'''1974''': He talked all of a hot afternoon, pushing his glasses onto his forehead, spreading his fingers, pouring ice water, spooning coffee into the '''ibrik'''. — Guy Davenport, ''Tatlin!''